cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it describes an attestation protocol and presents a tool-supported analysis of its security properties. It may also belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category as it uses logical formulas to annotate the protocol and reason about its properties. Additionally, it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category as it involves the design and analysis of a software protocol. The cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category is also a possibility as the protocol involves communication between multiple parties. Finally, it may belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category as it involves the formalization and analysis of a protocol using a tool.
